And you're doing this.

00:38:18.440 --> 00:38:19.280
You're not crying.

00:38:19.280 --> 00:38:20.560
You're not calling home.

00:38:20.560 --> 00:38:22.360
You're not wanting.

00:38:22.360 --> 00:38:24.960
He said, my keep brother couldn't do this.

00:38:24.960 --> 00:38:27.320
He said, I wish he could see you and see how well

00:38:27.320 --> 00:38:29.080
you're handling this.

00:38:29.080 --> 00:38:32.000
And get into Germany.

00:38:32.000 --> 00:38:34.400
Somebody was always there.

00:38:34.400 --> 00:38:40.200
I tell KSC's, if you're respectful, you're honest,

00:38:40.200 --> 00:38:43.400
and kind, people look after you.

00:38:43.400 --> 00:38:46.720
And everywhere I went, there was always an older person who

00:38:46.720 --> 00:38:48.680
said, we're going to take care of you.

00:38:48.680 --> 00:38:49.960
Because they saw how young I was.

00:38:49.960 --> 00:38:51.640
And they make sure that nothing happened to me.

00:38:54.520 --> 00:38:56.240
So that was my German experience.

00:38:56.240 --> 00:38:58.840
And did you get out and travel much while you were overseas?

00:38:58.840 --> 00:39:01.080
No, it didn't travel much in Germany.

