I got introduced to jazz.

00:41:25.440 --> 00:41:30.040
Matter of fact, I, the friend of mine that I met

00:41:30.040 --> 00:41:31.120
that introduced me to jazz.

00:41:31.120 --> 00:41:33.240
I actually saw him for the one years later,

00:41:33.240 --> 00:41:37.240
last year, for the first time since he left Germany.

00:41:37.240 --> 00:41:39.840
So, you know, I got introduced to jazz.

00:41:39.840 --> 00:41:44.200
Basically, it's a country where you Western music and rock

00:41:44.200 --> 00:41:46.200
and roll, the rock and roll, the type of bridge.

00:41:46.200 --> 00:41:47.520
Never heard of jazz.

00:41:47.520 --> 00:41:49.600
And I got introduced to jazz for these people,

00:41:49.600 --> 00:41:50.640
those kinds of things.

00:41:50.640 --> 00:41:53.840
And talking about what they did there and what was available

00:41:53.840 --> 00:41:56.760
there, of course, not all of it was true.

00:41:56.760 --> 00:42:00.680
But, you know, it gave you something to look forward to.

00:42:00.680 --> 00:42:02.200
Yeah.

00:42:02.200 --> 00:42:04.640
So I needed, I knew I needed an education to get

00:42:04.640 --> 00:42:06.480
